    {
        "content": "<p>alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12689#discussion_r2865918528\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The specific case that I ran into updating Spin was that a <code>Trap</code> in Wasmtime was converted to <code>wasmtime::Error</code> and then that was converted to <code>anyhow::Error</code>. Calling <code>anyhow_error.downcast::&lt;Trap&gt;()</code> was failing due to being created from <code>anyhow::Error::from_boxed</code> which ends up severing any <code>downcast</code> methods.</p>\n<p>So I believe what you've gisted will solve anyhow-and-back but wouldn't solve acquiring Wasmtime's error types which never went through <code>anyhow</code></p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 576337978,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1772221490
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>alexcrichton submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12689#pullrequestreview-3868751571\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 576338180,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1772221567
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12689#discussion_r2865923125\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>That's a good point, and yeah I think hooking <code>is</code> and <code>downcast</code> and friends with type parameters to explicitly handle the <code>anyhow</code> special case is the only way to go here. I'll see if I can't hook that up.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 576338183,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1772221567
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>fitzgen created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12689#discussion_r2865928557\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>That's a good point, and yeah I think hooking <code>is</code> and <code>downcast</code> and friends with type parameters to explicitly handle the <code>anyhow</code> special case is the only way to go here. I'll see if I can't hook that up.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Fine to do as a follow up too, ofc, if you prefer</p>\n</blockquote>",
